<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="720" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1074,1043,1355]" pageId="25" pageNumber="720">
COMMENTS: This new species resembles 
<emphasis box="[669,795,1043,1067]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="720">X. uniforme</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="LOBL, I." box="[803,920,1043,1067]" pageId="25" pageNumber="720" pagination="471 - 627" refId="ref13929" refString="LOBL, I. 1992. The Scaphidiidae (Coleoptera) of the Nepal Himalaya. Revue suisse de Zoologie 99: 471 - 627." type="journal article" year="1992">Löbl, 1992</bibRefCitation>
by its comparatively large size and by the color of the body, in combination with the elytra having complete and joined basal and sutural striae. 
<taxonomicName authority="(Vinson, 1943)" baseAuthorityName="Vinson" baseAuthorityYear="1943" box="[637,1048,1107,1131]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xotidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="720" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mauritianum">
<emphasis box="[637,880,1107,1131]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="720">Xotidium mauritianum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="VINSON, J." box="[896,1039,1107,1131]" pageId="25" pageNumber="720" pagination="177 - 209" refId="ref13981" refString="VINSON, J. 1943. The Scaphidiidae of Mauritius. The Mauritius Institute Bulletin 2 (3): 177 - 209." type="journal article" year="1943">Vinson, 1943</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
is almost as large and has also unicolored body, but differs drastically from its congeners by the shortened sutural striae and the absence of basal striae (see 
<bibRefCitation author="VINSON, J." box="[888,1057,1171,1195]" pageId="25" pageNumber="720" pagination="177 - 209" refId="ref13981" refString="VINSON, J. 1943. The Scaphidiidae of Mauritius. The Mauritius Institute Bulletin 2 (3): 177 - 209." type="journal article" year="1943">VINSON, 1943</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lobl" authorityYear="2011" box="[151,381,1203,1227]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Xotidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="720" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tubuliferum">
<emphasis box="[151,381,1203,1227]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="720">Xotidium tubuliferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be distinguished easily by its aedeagus lacking sclerotized flagellum, and by the long widened apical section of the parameres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1074,1043,1355]" pageId="25" pageNumber="720">Both available males have completely extruded internal sac of the aedeagus. It consists of a simple tube narrowed in middle, longer than the entire median lobe. Very fine, spine-like structures are present in its basal part.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
